article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 62, W. Michigan 59
article.story: OXFORD, Ohio (AP) -- Doug Penno hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer to give Miami (Ohio) a 62-59 victory over Western Michigan on Saturday night. Western Michigan (10-12, 5-4 Mid-American Conference) led by as many as 16 points in the first half before scrambling back to pull even at 59-59 on two free throws by Shawntes Gary with 20 seconds left. The RedHawks (10-11, 6-3) brought the ball down the floor before calling a timeout with 14 seconds left, then worked the ball around until Alex Moosmann's pass set up Penno for his game-winning jumper. Tim Pollitz led the RedHawks with 20 points, with Nathan Peavy adding 19 and Penno finishing with 12. They hit 68 percent of their shots from the field in the second half after trailing 33-19 at halftime. Joe Reitz scored 14 points and Gary added 13 for the Broncos. Miami hit just 1 of 10 3-pointers in the first half but was 6 of 9 behind the arc in the second half.
